tragedy /ˈtrædʒɪdɪ/

(tragedies) 

1. N-VAR A tragedy is an extremely sad event or situation. 灾难 

例： They have suffered an enormous personal tragedy. 他们遭受了一场巨大的个人灾难。 

2. N-VAR Tragedy is a type of literature, especially drama, that is serious and sad, and often ends with the death of the main character. 悲剧 

例： The story has elements of tragedy and farce. 这个故事含有悲剧和闹剧的成分。

